featured_reviews.review_id:
I love sunnath jamath
The Jamaat Ahle Sunnat (Urdu: jm`t hli snt) is a Muslim religious organization in Pakistan that represents the Barelvi movement. It was supported by Muhammad Shafee Okarvi.[1] As a Sunni organisation it has adopted many Sufi customs and traditions.[2]

In 2006, a bomb attack on a Jamaat Ahle Sunnat organised event to celebrate the mawlid (birthday of the Islamic prophet Muhammad) in Karachi killed at least 63 people and injured over 80.[3][4] Among the dead were several Barelvi religious figures, including the senior leadership of Jamaat Ahle Sunnat and Sunni Tehreek.[5] Three men said to belong to the Lashkar-e-Jhangvi were indicted for the crime
